The paper deals with the problem of recovering frequency-sparse signals from a subset of regularly spaced samples, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also establishes a link between CCS and LRMC, which involves matrix completion, and hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes practical algorithms for solving the problem, which involves optimization techniques, and hence, cs.MM (Mathematical Optimization) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also likely sub-categories.
